cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.MM

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision and image processing, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) category. The use of self-attention mechanisms and multi-scale style swap also suggests that it may fall under the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) category. The paper also involves the development of a new model, which could place it in the cs.LG (Machine Learning) category. The use of different stroke patterns and spatial regions in the output image could also suggest that it falls under the cs.GR (Graphics) category. Finally, the use of multiple feature maps and flexible fusion strategies could suggest that it belongs to the cs.MM (Multimedia) category.
